{\footnote # IDH_CSHARP_07}
{\footnote $ C# - Classes et orientation objet}
{\footnote K C# classes objets;heritage;polymorphisme;abstract virtual override sealed;proprietes;init-only;required;indexers;constructeurs primaires;interfaces;default interface methods;structs;readonly struct;record struct}
\b\fs24 Classes et orientation objet \b0\fs20\par
\par
7.1 Definition de classe\par
\par
{\f1   public class Personne \{}\par
{\f1     public string Nom \{ get; set; \}}\par
{\f1     public int Age \{ get; init; \}     // C# 9+ init-only}\par
\par
{\f1     public Personne(string nom, int age) \{}\par
{\f1       Nom = nom;}\par
{\f1       Age = age;}\par
{\f1     \}}\par
\par
{\f1     public override string ToString() => $"\{Nom\} (\{Age\})";}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
7.2 Heritage et polymorphisme\par
\par
{\f1   public abstract class Forme \{}\par
{\f1     public abstract double Aire();}\par
{\f1     public virtual string Nom() => "Forme";}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
{\f1   public class Cercle : Forme \{}\par
{\f1     public double Rayon \{ get; set; \}}\par
{\f1     public override double Aire() => Math.PI * Rayon * Rayon;}\par
{\f1     public override string Nom() => "Cercle";}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
Modificateurs d'acces : public, private, protected, internal,\par
protected internal, private protected, file (C# 11+).\par
\par
Mots-cles : abstract, virtual, override, sealed, new, static, partial.\par
\par
7.3 Proprietes\par
\par
{\f1   public class Compteur \{}\par
{\f1     private int _valeur;}\par
{\f1     public int Valeur \{}\par
{\f1       get => _valeur;}\par
{\f1       set \{ if (value >= 0) _valeur = value; \}}\par
{\f1     \}}\par
{\f1     public int Suivant => _valeur + 1;     // expression-bodied}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
Auto-properties : public int X \{ get; set; \}\par
Init-only : public int X \{ get; init; \}\par
Required (C# 11+) : public required string Nom \{ get; init; \}\par
\par
7.4 Indexers\par
\par
{\f1   public class Tableau \{}\par
{\f1     private int[] _data = new int[100];}\par
{\f1     public int this[int i] \{}\par
{\f1       get => _data[i];}\par
{\f1       set => _data[i] = value;}\par
{\f1     \}}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
7.5 Constructeurs primaires (C# 12+)\par
\par
{\f1   public class Point(double x, double y) \{}\par
{\f1     public double X => x;}\par
{\f1     public double Y => y;}\par
{\f1     public double Distance() => Math.Sqrt(x*x + y*y);}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
7.6 Interfaces\par
\par
{\f1   public interface IComparable<T> \{}\par
{\f1     int CompareTo(T autre);}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
Default interface methods (C# 8+) :\par
{\f1   public interface ILog \{}\par
{\f1     void Log(string msg);}\par
{\f1     void LogErreur(string msg) => Log("ERREUR: " + msg);  // par defaut}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
7.7 Structs\par
\par
{\f1   public struct Point \{ public int X, Y; \}}\par
\par
Readonly struct (C# 7.2+) :\par
{\f1   public readonly struct Vector3 \{}\par
{\f1     public readonly double X, Y, Z;}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
Record struct (C# 10+) :\par
{\f1   public record struct Coord(double Lat, double Lon);}\par
\par
\par
\par
